        <div type="translation">
            <ab>P. L. Bat. 25 62 (English)

                                        To my lord and brother Alexander the monthly president and his associates of the guild of canvas and carpet workers from Heraclius the systates greetings. I have cancelled the name of Antinous, son of Heraclides, on account of the anabolikon tax of the thirteenth indiction, because I have no claim whatsoever on him on account of the said tax of his.
                                        I Heraclius the systates have signed.</ab>
        </div>
